Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine half the garlic and the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%grams}. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Streaky Bacon{4%rasher} and fry until crispy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer them to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Put the pan back on medium-high heat (add an extra drizzle of @oil{} if needed), lay in the burgers and fry until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} in total. Carefully turn them every 3-4 mins and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers are cooked, transfer them to a plate lined with kitchen paper alongside the bacon rashers and set aside for now.

Pop the empty frying pan back onto medium-high heat with another drizzle of @oil{} (if needed).

Stir in the remaining garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}. Add the @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and stir fry for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliters} and @Sugar for the Sauce{1/2%tsp}.

> See pantry for water and sugar amounts.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then simmer until the sauce thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the tomato sauce has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%grams} and half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams}. Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Meanwhile, halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Pop onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the burgers back into the pan and gently turn in the sauce until warmed through and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the burger buns between your plates.

Top the bases with the sausage burgers, 2 bacon rashers and spoon over the remaining sauce. Drizzle over the @Fresh Pesto{32%grams} and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.

Sandwich together with the bun lids and serve with the chips alongside.

> Enjoy!